<p>18 July 1915<br/>Sunday<br/>7th After Trinity</p>
<p>On account of a late issue of rations I miss church parade.<br/>A huge pile of mail arrives but proves to be all old letters returned to us after being re-sorted.<br/>Working party from 4 pm to 8 pm making ledges or terraces on the hill side for the accommodation of a lot of troops who are to arrive here shortly one man wounded</p>
<p>1915 July 19<br/>Monday</p>
<p>No rations at all this morning A.S.C. are taking stock.<br/>take on the same job as yesterday</p>
